This paper is about improving dependency parsing, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as bidirectional LSTM and dynamic programming, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper introduces a new algorithm for non-projective parsing, which involves computational complexity analysis, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the empirical evaluation of the proposed method, which involves statistical analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible sub-category.
